# Next.js Architecture

- Use Next.js App Router with TypeScript strict mode
- Use Tailwind CSS v4 for all styling
- Default to Server Components; only use `"use client"` for forms, animations, or state management
- Never hardcode content in components — all data must flow through props

## File Organization

```
app/
├── layout.tsx              (fonts, root metadata)
├── page.tsx                (homepage)
├── sitemap.ts              (dynamic sitemap)
├── robots.ts               (robots config)
├── (pages)/layout.tsx      (shared Header/Footer wrapper)
└── api/forms/submit/route.ts

components/
├── [feature-name]/         (grouped by feature, e.g. components/service-detail/)
└── ui/                     (shared reusable components)

lib/
├── data/                   (all content — easy CMS swap later)
├── types/                  (TypeScript interfaces)
└── seo/                    (metadata + JSON-LD helpers)
```

## Code Quality

- Write semantic HTML (`nav`, `main`, `section`, `article`, `aside`)
- Mobile-first responsive design (Tailwind: `sm:`, `md:`, `lg:`, `xl:`)
- Proper TypeScript types — never use `any`
- Graceful error handling with `try/catch` and fallbacks
- ARIA labels for accessibility
- Keep components under 200 lines; split if larger
- kebab-case filenames, PascalCase components
